Hi,

when I try to load the konnov reaction mechanism(with python) I get an
error:
Procedure: installReaction
Error:   Undeclared duplicate reactions detected: 
Reaction 10: H + O2 (+ M) <=> HO2 (+ M)
Reaction 11: H + O2 (+ AR) <=> HO2 (+ AR)

A look at the input file shows:
H+O2(+M)=HO2(+M)               1.480E+12      0.6         0.0 
    LOW /3.50E+16 -0.41 -1116.0/ 
    TROE /0.5 100000 10/
 AR/0.0/ H2O/10.6/ H2/1.5/ CO2/2.4/ 
H+O2(+AR)=HO2(+AR)             1.480E+12      0.6         0.0
    LOW /7.00E+17 -0.8  0.0/
    TROE /0.45 10 100000/ 

I earlier cantera-versions this mechanism worked, what do you suggest
? Is now the "duplicate"-statement needed ? (The mechanism is
converted to .cti with ck2cti.exe.)

ulf
